{ screens.ps1 #screens-ps1

 `screens.ps1` is a → Windows/PowerShell script that prints the connected monitors' dimensions and positions.
  gh|scripts-and-utilities|/screens.ps1||

  → https://github.com/ReneNyffenegger/scripts-and-utilities/commit/d2982a9349f2bd0a614e67c66bdab5bf6db6ce35[Version 2] of the script shows both,
  the full dimensions and the working area's dimensions.

